Package frames.input.event

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    KeyEvent
    A key-event is an Event specialization that encapsulates a KeyShortcut.
    KeyShortcut
    This class represents KeyEvent shortcuts.
    MotionEvent
    Base class of all motion events defined from DOFs (degrees-of-freedom).
    MotionEvent1
    A MotionEvent with one degree of freedom (MotionEvent1.x()).
    MotionEvent2
    A MotionEvent with two degrees-of-freedom (MotionEvent2.x() and MotionEvent2.y()).
    MotionEvent3
    A MotionEvent with three degrees-of-freedom ( MotionEvent3.x(), MotionEvent3.y() and MotionEvent3.z() ).
    MotionEvent6
    A MotionEvent with six degrees-of-freedom ( MotionEvent6.x(), MotionEvent6.y(), MotionEvent6.z() , MotionEvent6.rx(), MotionEvent6.ry() and MotionEvent6.rz()).
    TapEvent
    A tap event encapsulates a TapShortcut and it's defined by the number of taps.
    TapShortcut
    This class represents TapEvent shortcuts.
